00:57:38.770 --> 00:57:42.350
And then finally, I want to quickly talk
about myths versus facts.

00:57:42.360 --> 00:57:45.340
And, you know,
it's pretty funny because I talk to,

00:57:45.450 --> 00:57:47.860
you know, again,
some pretty large companies.

00:57:47.860 --> 00:57:51.460
And, you know,
there's a lot of people think that AFP,

00:57:51.460 --> 00:57:55.180
the Apple Filing Protocol,
is basically Apple Talk.

00:57:55.260 --> 00:57:58.560
And just, again, to make sure that,
you know, we've gone away from

00:57:58.560 --> 00:58:00.230
Apple Talk years ago,
right?

00:58:00.330 --> 00:58:02.330
So there is no more
Apple Talk running on the network.

00:58:02.400 --> 00:58:06.300
So AFP is like SMB for the PC, right?

00:58:06.340 --> 00:58:08.640
It's pure TCP IP protocol.

00:58:08.640 --> 00:58:10.900
There's no Apple Talk going
on on the network.

00:58:10.900 --> 00:58:13.940
So that's just, you know, for you,
if your network person, you know,

00:58:13.950 --> 00:58:15.890
tells you, you know,
we don't like Macs because

00:58:15.890 --> 00:58:17.530
they still run Apple Talk,
we really don't.

00:58:17.620 --> 00:58:19.900
SMB is faster than AFP.

00:58:19.900 --> 00:58:20.930
That is not the case.

00:58:20.940 --> 00:58:24.080
And, you know, really, we've tuned AFP.

00:58:24.080 --> 00:58:27.020
Because our customers work
with really large files,

00:58:27.100 --> 00:58:29.650
you're always better
using AFP when you can.

00:58:29.660 --> 00:58:35.140
And even today on the Mac OS X side,
it's always better to use an

00:58:35.140 --> 00:58:36.260
XServe to serve your network.

00:58:36.340 --> 00:58:41.000
Simply because the protocol has
evolved throughout the years.

00:58:41.190 --> 00:58:44.880
You still, you know, Microsoft still uses
AFP 2.2 on their servers.

00:58:44.880 --> 00:58:49.030
And that is just not the,
it's just not a good protocol to use,

00:58:49.250 --> 00:58:50.960
especially when people
are running Photoshop,

00:58:50.960 --> 00:58:53.500
InDesign, and all those big
applications on a daily basis.

00:58:53.500 --> 00:58:56.560
And then they still have to deal
with resource and data forks.

00:58:56.560 --> 00:59:01.080
So really, it's better to have the
Mac connect to AFP than SMB.

00:59:01.080 --> 00:59:03.080
AFP is chatty, not at all.

00:59:03.080 --> 00:59:05.760
That, you know,
that used to be the case with Apple Talk.

00:59:06.340 --> 00:59:08.580
But, you know,
NetBIOS was also very chatty.

00:59:08.580 --> 00:59:10.150
But AFP is not chatty.

00:59:10.310 --> 00:59:13.250
Okay, again,
people confuse Apple Talk with AFP.

00:59:13.260 --> 00:59:16.220
And then Rendezvous is
proprietary or chatty.

